Review: Great location! It's just off the freeway behind Oxford Suites. There are a couple restaurants right next to it but if you walk South and cross overland you will find better options. There's a small patch of grass where you can let your dog out and stretch their legs. And a restroom downstairs in the hotel or walk over to Lowe's.
Ok, 3a wasn't working well for me. It stopped charging several times. Even after unplug and replug. Tried another and it was fine. Got 145kw. Pretty busy. Bathroom is in basement of hotel btw.

Supercharger is in the Oxford Suites hotel parking lot.  The side door closest to the charger may be locked so I had to go through the front door and walk by the front desk liked I owned the place lol.  Bathrooms are not on the ground floor.  Stairs were "blocked" to get to the basement where the bathroom is.  So taking the elevator just past the front desk might be the better option.  Ice machine on the first floor was helpful for me.

I live in the city of Buffalo and these chargers are down/unavailable more than they are available. Oftentimes, there's only one charger available for use making it especially difficult for people who visit this area and have no other alternatives. These chargers malfunction during colder months, y'all gotta work that out because the temps in Buffalo can get frigid. The availability of chargers should also be transparent via internet search engines (Google, Bing, etc.) and not only using your app. I've spoken to many nice out-of-town folks (some who don't speak fluent English -add more language selections on the stations) who go into panic mode when they can't charge their vehicle because chargers are limited. I always offer up mine because I am closer to home and never want to experience what that feels like. The demand for EV's doesn't align with the supply of charging stations and/or the amount of kWh sometimes promised per charge. There's too much stress and pressure on consumers and not enough action taken by Companies who should be making the transition from gas to an EV easier. The goal for creating a cleaner Earth is a bit one-sided. You have to supply better chargers if you really want to "Electrify America".

Quick and easy. Was able to bring my car and charge it without having to wait for a charger. Plenty of spots in the lot to charge. Definitely would come back here.
Well marked, conveniently close to Gessner entrance, with multiple designated parking areas and types of chargers

Contrary to the photo evidence there are two CHAdeMO / CCS chargers at this location. The chargers are sponsored by the Village of Marble Cliff and are free to use.  The brand is ChargePoint, which has an App for your smartphone that can be used to start the charging process. If your phone has Near Field Communications enabled it can be used like a RFID card to get the charging station started if the ChargePoint App is installed and running. The only caveat to this location is the designated parking spots are a little unwieldy for charging a Nissan Leaf with the front charge ports. The cords reach better if you go one spot to the left of the designated parking spots
I haven't seen any other cars using these when I've gone in the evenings. Seems like fast charging at a fairly cheap rate.
Good parking spot

I charge here frequently there is always chargers available, I‚Äôve never gone here and not been able to charge. I usually go around 3:30 - 4:30 after I leave work always great conversations around the color of my car as well lol. Tesla Owners are very friendly we talk to everyone, say hello I‚Äôll speak, 1 of these things do not match the others lol.
Used to be pretty packed, until they added more Superchargers (250kw) at Sheetz (just down the road) and Royal Farms (Urbana).

Beware that Google maps has the location slightly wrong. You need to enter the Premium Outlets and the chargers are located on the outer parking lot close to the Michael Kors store. If you follow Google maps you'll find yourself entering I-270 with no way back!

As others have mentioned - please use Logan's Roadhouse for routing on your GPS, as the station is located next to the restaurant! The actual station itself worked fine, and my car was able to charge at near the rated speed of 150kW. Nothing close by to do unless you want to grab a bite at the restaurant next door.

I charge my EQS twice a week for 30 min and it's been perfect every time except on 9/24 when the system stopped charging after a few minutes. Had enough charge to last so left and went back the next day and it was perfect. I'll start charging my Lucid there next week. I've seen Kia, F150, and Rivian owners charging without issue. Now, if they had more chargers available across the main travel routes, EVs would be able to go mainstream instead of restricted to tech types and early adopters like me.
Hard to find and need to back up into traffic through the shopping center to get to the chargers. Speed is as advertised though

Have charged here before, but today Ko e ChadeMo charger did not work.  My experience with EVgo Chademo chargers in both NC and GA over the past year 07/2021 to 07/2022 is that they only work about 50% of the time.  I'm glad I got to use some of the credit that came with my Nissan Leaf purchase, but the fact that it expires is really disappointing.  All that to say: I will never plan to charge at another EVgo station ever again.  Only if its my only option I will cross my fingers and hope that their unreliable chargers will work at even a 19kwh rate, much less the expectedit, full advertised 50kwh.

First time utilizing this SC location and it was great - very chill and easy to get in and out. And I love that if you're just there to charge, you don't have to pay the parking garage rate so long as you're out before 2 hrs (new supercharger in Decatur is not as generous). I was charged up in 35 min and I will never not be happy seeing how little you pay vs. gas.

Tesla navigation is accurate, led me right to P2 level. After you take your ticket, make the first right at the stop and you'll see a small red Tesla sign on a pillar to your left. Keep going straight and you can't miss all the stalls. Happy charging~

This parking garage Supercharger station reminds me of a scene from a distopian movie. It's huge with about 21 chargers. If you need to stretch your legs, there's a Publix and shops above and within walking distance. As you enter the parking garage don't dismay, the first two hours are free. You should be charged and ready within that window of time.
All 4 stalls working, just wishing there is a 350kW here

This is my favorite supercharger spot that I've been too. Can't beat a Bucees...  The charging was fast and not many stalls in use.

The only mild complaint I could mention is that it's a longish walk back and forth from the store without much in the way of pedestrian markings, walkways or anything. Just keep looking around and stay safe while you get a lovely kolache and brisket sammie!

Nothing beats ChargePoint service. Professional, convenient, and reliable. The only problem encountered is when the owner does not honor their contract with ChargePoint and starts to operate the charger preferentially allowing certain vehicles to charge while preventing/towing others. These unfair practices are not under ChargePoint control and undetectable on their end.
Located right beside Carowinds entrance, Infront of Comfort Inn at exit 90 with 12 level III 250kW charging stations, Clean and convenient!!!

More banks than I expected- for the area seemed like a pretty large Supercharger site. They are all a longer than necessary walk to the store, probably because all the truck nuts will get angry and park in them. I'll walk, but I wish it didn't have to be like this because people are small sometimes.
Located behind Black Bear Dinner.
Chargers all worked as intended. In fact there were plenty of EV vehicles using this charging station. Got a full charge and continued on our trip to Washington.
Plenty of charging stations but it doesn't feel like a safe environment
All reviews correct. Just did a PA-AZ round trip and best charging site I‚Äôve visited! Max‚Äôs treats you like royalty. Worth a stop even if you don‚Äôt need it.
Decent charge and fee, not fast charging.
Great spot. Gen 2 chargers that share with the adjacent car. Decent charging rate when not full or at least sharing with others. Waited for 5 cars on a Sunday afternoon.

In a convenient store parking lot right off the highway. But tucked in the side and not looking too safe to be here at night. Pros apart from the convenient store is it's a 250kwh charger and it's close enough to Greenville to have a 2nd Supercharger location.
Stella's restaurant is really close and ups store near by. Great place to recharge.

Great place to charge, 8 stalls at 150kW, currently .31 cents a kWh. It is downtown and there are shops and food readily available. There are public free rest rooms in the center of town within the park.
Really great place to stop for Tesla drivers. Near downtown Sulpher Springs, so you can easily get dinner at a local spot. There have always been plenty of open chargers each time I visit.
This charger was convenient when I was visiting in NC. Very clean lot. Sheetz has decent food too.

Please be careful when charging at night. Tonight, there were two sketchy guys sitting in a black gas car parked directly at a supercharger. They stared the entire time while I was parking and every time I looked over, they tried to hide. I didn‚Äôt feel comfortable leaving the car but eventually, they drove across the street and watched from a distance. The parking lot was empty so they didn‚Äôt have a reason to park at the chargers. On the other hand, this location is great during the day.

Solid 250kw charge spot behind Sheetz. Clean bathroom, plenty of grab and go for long distance trips. Sheetz locations are far superior compared to hotel locations imo. People have reported the chargers not supporting 250kw but I assure you they are 250kw capable. See pictures for proof.
It was nice to see Speedway had multiple charging stations in place for electric cars
Secluded place to charge. Very convenient.
Fast charging and lots of charging spots
Great charging area but it would be more convenient if it was more centered to the mall
Charger is fast and has always been available and operational. Safe location.
Make sure you sign up for Autocharge+ to make the process super easy
Awesome chargers and bathrooms , popcorn and waiting area during the day
Charger is kinda hidden in the back of the dealership but fast charger! 2022 kia Niro EV charged at 47kW on combo

Out back of a Costco/Stop and Shop, by the dumpsters.  Pretty far from 90, Down a road that is very badly in need of repair, no other humans in sight, even at dusk.  It got the job done, but next time I'll plan to avoid this one.
Quick charger in good condition. Grab a donut while you wait!
150 kWh charges at the mall parking lot. No trash cans onsite, you'll need to wait to the mall if you need to discard trash.

Great location. Needs upkeep. 2 stalls are down and need cables replaced.
Due to the corner location, lots of trash and debris blow in to the lot‚Ä¶

Safe, fast enough, plenty to do while you charge.
Love the convenient location and its free. But, 3 were inoperable, and 3 were only 5 kW. I previously have charged here at 10 kW.
If you are into organic foods, vegetarian cuisine and juice bars, this is the place. A Whole Foods 365 store anchors the center. They have free charging stations for electric cars.

Nice little wholefoods store. Doesn't carry as much, so lines moved fast because they also have a self checkout.... You can get in and out pretty quickly. My only compliant is that items go out of stock fast. Security is inside, parking lot is structure well with lighting and ample space. Electric car charging available

Great spot for a Supercharger. Plenty of grass, to let out your dogs and a good amount of stores for snacks and a quick bite nearby including Walgreens, CVS, Walmart, a gas station, and Sonic. fast and moderately convenient. There are options in the area, you are not stranded if you need food or bathroom. If you like teenagers with loud mufflers driving in circles around town you are going to love this place. And it is near a store that only sells batteries.
Charged my mach e here. 4 tesla chargers and 4 J1772 chargers. On ground level of parking garage. Free. My mach e got 34 miles of range in an hour and a half.
Across the street from Taco Bell and other restaurants. Got the job done and good lunch
Good location right off I-12. Located in a shopping center parking lot with Target, Taco Bell, Chick-Fil-A and a gas station within walking distance.

Great spot for a charger! Would give 5 stars if there was a public restroom within walking distance. The Superchargers are located in a shopping center so there‚Äôs plenty to see and do if you‚Äôre not pressed for time. Really also liked how safe and clean this area was. Closest trash bins are next to Which Wich.
Conveniently located North of Hartford. Near to Pride store and deli.

Nice place to charge, while waiting you can grab food or visit bestbuy or across the street to the mall.

The cons? Sometimes even you are the only one in there the charging is very slow, it will take time to complete your charge even you have preheat your battery.

The cables are great and deluxe electric is provided to your car. I get an extra 300 horsepower when I charge here and it made my hair look better & my car is shinier too. Just kidding. Right next to Whole Foods is a bonus.  Machines were wicked finicky throwing errors but after 20 minutes we got it to work.  Credit card slider is blocked in the right one and does not work!  Use the app to pay.
Plenty of super chargers at a convenient distance to a restaurant/coffee shop.
Easy to find and a short drive to Dinkin Donuts that was open before 5 on a Sunday morning. Other than drinkers staggering out of Arch II sports bar it was pretty quiet.
I dont know why it says 250kw, everytime i use this i can only get 70kw, even preheated battery.  But when i go to west hartford station i get better charge.

This is one where you have to already have an account set up in chargepoint.com
Look for this sign and the charging station is directly behind this building.
Never had a problem here. Lots of chargers and under-ultilized. Supermarket, Asian food, and Donuts all in the strip mall. After hours would be bad, but during the day there are facilities.

Plenty of shopping close by while you charge.
Excellent location and very friendly diamond store. They always wave to me when I go charge my Tesla.
Great location but on 11/20/19 1A and 1B were not working, reported to Tesla.
Very fast charger. Plan ahead because this one doesn't have any food or drinks nearby.
Chademo Charger works and is well maintained. Though I have had problems getting the EVGO app/ card to work at this charger. It's not particularly cheap either.
Good charger, but this one costs money. No special parking lot access needed.

Great location (US 41 and I-4). We stopped by on a Sunday afternoon and there were only two other Teslas. Easy to get in and get out. Great food and drink options at Wawa. There was a chrome Tesla as well, which looked really nice as well!
Good supercharging location. Places to eat across the street or shop at Winn Dixie. Nice area in general.

No other EV manufacturer has a charging network as tightly integrated as Tesla. The car preconditions the battery for the fastest charging time and it automatically calculates  how long you need to charge before leaving for your next destination.  If you buy anything else you'll be hunting for chargers, trying to validate your account to enable charging and doing your own calculations about how long you'll need to charge. This is a new and exciting experience for me. The process is simple not too lengthy and accessible
Plenty of plug in stations. Walked to Starbucks and sat outside while charging.
Dorothy Lane Market: L2 48 amp Tesla chargers

Although station is in a convenient location.  Those CRUISE self driving cars take up most if not all of the spots.  If you are in a rush plan on waiting at least 30 minutes just for one of them to leave.

I‚Äôve used this charger about 15 times just enough to make it back to downtown Phoenix and it has worked with fast charging each time with the exception of the first time I used it because the cord had been parked on so it had to be fixed. My biggest issues is people sitting idle and not charging and the company doesn‚Äôt charge for idle time so some people have no urgency. Charger now has not been powered for over a month for some reason so you can‚Äôt pay via the app with your credit card linked.

The single charger is in the middle of the parking lot. Luckily, we arrived on almost no charge. Shortly after we got there two more people also wanted to use the charger, but only one can charge at a time. Getting the charger started was not intuitive. I installed the app and was able to sign up for an account, but it was so hot that my location services weren't working on my phone, so I couldn't use the app to start charging. I called the number on the charger and they stated it remotely, guiding me through the steps to get it working. After 20 minutes on the fast charger, my car was charged 20%, which was enough to get home. It cost about $8. After I was done and put the handle back in the charger, it wouldn't recognize that it was disconnected. I called customer service again. They couldn't get that fixed, but it was asking me to authorize again if I tried to start, so I left because I wouldn't be charged for someone else charging.  I'm glad the charging station was available, but it wasn't a simple process to use it.

Getting account setup with payment method requires email activation first which required a call to support to figure out, as it kept failing to add card. Figuring out what to press in the app to get charging started was non intuitive (you have to click the charge adapter to start with no interface prompt). Charging session continued to fault in first five minutes and required a restart of the session, multiple times as it would drop from 33kw to 14kw on 2020 Model 3 (ultimately could not get it to not fault in the car even after contacting support to reboot the whole unit, so charge speeds drop to 14kw and stabilize). The connectivity between the app and charger was buggy to get it first started. Overall mediocre experience, but happy to see more chargers in the area and 14kw is better than nothing. Support was quick to answer on both calls which was nice. Their website is not clear if there is a dedicated Tesla charger or not (I thought it might require the CHAdeMO adapter, but there is a dedicated Tesla plug!). The app better shows what adapters are for sure at the station.
Always a great charging experience at these super chargers!
Great mix of dining options. However, your chest will charge faster than you can eat your food.
This spot has multiple charging stations, the one I use is the fast charging one. It's easy to get and easy to charge the car. The only reason why its not a 5 star is because it's expensive.

Very easy access next to the Albertsons shopping center. Nice convenient location. In N Out right across the street.

Great place to charge there is usually a charger open every time we go.
Only one plug, payment required

It's fine.
One of the units wouldn't connect to my car.

This is in the parking lot of a Bank of America.
It is an easy walk to the Kent Station mall and the library.
Easy access right off of I-5, charging works with RFID card. 2x Tesla plugs, 2x CCS plugs, 2x CHADEMO plugs, and 2x J1772 plugs. 50kWh max.
A few stations were not working, but the ones that did were great!  Pushed 150kW.  Wal‚Ä¢Mart close by = great location.
Many empty place and many fast food available around

Been reliable charge station for me so far‚Ä¶ for now. Strangely however, there are usually non electric cars parked here. Thankfully they move when I arrive. I find that charging up to 85 %, then the rest at home does the trick. It‚Äôs faster than trying to complete the 95% in the hour.

Chargers are in good shape. Cost is okay. Easy to access. 50kW charger max cost is $0.56kW during peak and $0.99 session fee. Works good with the EVGO app so no need to mess with credit cards and just get billed once a month
Had problems requiring me to call number. They fixed it and then charged ok.
Nice to know that there are 2 fast charge stations here. Enter through the Motel 6 entrance and it will be down a short hill on the left.
These stations  work! Amazing!

Always in good condition
Level 2 fast charger ... Seamless connection through evgo app. Loved it.
Easy access from the freeway. Target and In-N-Out are in the same parking lot, making it a great place to stop!
Wow!  300 miles per hour!  Charging at home is 4 miles per hour.  Very fast charging.
Always has one available.  Clean and safe

Very unreliable! There have been days I've been at this location and only 2 charging stations worked. Then there have been days when all 4 charging stations worked!!! There have been days when I've waited over 15 minutes for a charging station. Electrify America doesn't have many stations within proximity to one another in these areas - Menifee, Murrieta, Lake Elsinore; and NOTHING in Perris or Temecula!!!

I don't know why this station gets poor reviews. There are 8 stations. Not sure if there is a Tesla charger but they have the other two. It's in the back side of the mall. Love this spot! Nice little creek area to look at. Can‚Äôt really explore in there because of the lushness of it all and litter but better than always staring at the concrete jungle! Outlet mall is right here to walk around as well! This is great!

The few chargers here are often available in the evenings. Fast charge at 50kwh works well. As with most charge point screens, the buttons are not always working great and this one needs to be tapped about 1 inch below the on-screen button. Using the apps makes this a non-issue

Also Tesla navigation tells you to take exit 25, but it‚Äôs easier to just drive into the Rest Area - the chargers (and ChargePoint units) are on the right before the rest stop building.
Great chargers. Lots of non electric cars parked here though

Small charging station with a few slots.  Conveniently located just off the freeway, easy to find, and clean.  There are places you can go to for a bite to eat, in the same parking lot, while charging your car.

Not much to review. It charges my car. Does it fast. Haven‚Äôt died yet from electrocution but when I do I‚Äôll let everyone know
Free charge-point charging station right next to Meijer.  2 stalls with 30A service.
Yes it is a zoo. Yes it will take a while to get to the restroom.  Yes there is chaos. Yes it is fun.
Two Tesla chargers at the back of the Homewood Suites. Used while on a road trip and was fully charged by morning.
Good station. App needed to start charge. 150kw max

This is a great location with plenty of open stalls they will never probably be a lot of Teslas here unless they have a Tesla meet up here. I‚Äôm hoping soon that tesla charging station will be just like gas stations with a convenient store in bathrooms.

Located in the employee's parking üÖøÔ∏è lot at the City üèôÔ∏è of Portsmouth Municipal Building üè¢, I believe it's intended for the hybrid or electric ‚ö° cars that the city uses. It has the capacity to charge two vehicles simultaneously.
Right inside the entrance. Both chargers were open and the price is reasonable.

Trip saver between Memphis and Hammond / New Orleans.

Was able to charge multiple times at 80-82 KW

Fast charger, not crowded at all, good charge speeds through out.
It is in the parking lot of a outlet mall, so there are stores and bathrooms decently close by. Also lots of trash cans on the sidewalk in front of stores, but none at the chargers themselves. Glad Tesla placed a SC in Vicksburg MS. Used it today and it charged my M3 quickly.

Nice, quiet corner of town, next to a gas station store, across the street from a restaurant.

There's only two charging working at this time and the other two seem to have difficulty in just turning them on you have to shake the handle to get it working so don't give up if you plan to come here know that the charging station seems to be operational but I wouldn't be surprised if he doesn't work for you it seems to be under construction only two of them work. This is a great place to park to charge your truck or car whatever and to use the bathroom or even better take a shower I think it's like 15 bucks this is a truck stop which means it's open 24/7 so you can pretty much charge your truck or RV and not worry too much about safety very safe place so if you are planning on charging I recommend this place I slept here all night it's very clean and safe but I would not recommend this during winter.

The j1772 port worked well for an overnight/destination charge for my tesla. Concrete block was a bit weird but could still easily reach the charge port.

Updated 07/12/2022: The concrete blocks have been removed! Thanks for your responsiveness. Max charge is still 28kw but still far preferable to 6kw.
Desperate for a charge and this was our only option. Max charge was 28kw. Short cable. The cement blocks in front of the charge units force parking a little too far for the cable length, and the height could really damage a vehicle.
On the plus side, the Town Pump is a nice amenity with clean restrooms and plenty of food.
New V3 Supercharger in Auburn! Very convenient location.
Very, very nice to have one in Auburn near the mall. Usually there's one or two other cars. Sometime there are no others. I go every couple of weeks.
Zero friction. Thanks, ChargePoint!

I left my wallet at the house but was able to get an account set up and started charging quickly. Of course my wife was able to read the card info to me but o set up the account. This station also takes cards without an account

One of the 350 posts only dispensed 10kw. Changed posts and maxed out my car.

Also, you can charge EVERY modern EV here. CCS and Chademo.

Wide open chargers, but the area was busy.  Picnic tables nearby with a little shade.
Convenient place off I-70 with large number of chargers, super fast and the kicker, cheaper electric rates.
Easy access from highway. I think it is a great idea to put superchargers next to gas stations with good amenities. The gas station store is nice, good bakery and coffee.
Good location. Meijer gas station has bathrooms and $1 sodas
Great location lots of food options nearby, I hope they upgrade this to the 250kw version 3 chargers soon, would love a bit more speed.
This one seems a little slow at least today. Says it‚Äôs 150kw but only getting 64k max. Not mad about it but just something to keep in mind if your picking one in the Indy area.

Actually visited the Sheetz gas station at which the Tesla Superchargers are located....did not use the "superchargers", but did use the facilities at the Sheetz station....this seems to be an older Sheetz location, and it is showing its age....the inside of the store was not very well lighted, and seemed sort of dreary....the mens room was in need of a good cleaning...I ordered a burger; it was served barely warm (I picked up my order as soon as it was called) and the meat patties (I ordered "double meat") were tasteless, and looked more gray than brown. Charging speed was ok for us - not as slow as others reported. Really nice spot - lots of grass for dog, picnic tables, swing set. There is a pizza place (Prairie Pizza), but it wasn‚Äôt open when we were there.

Didn't work for my Chevy Spark EV. I had planned a route to Salem for my nephew's 2nd birthday. I was excited because this was a new charger and was just the right distance to make it only 3 charging stops, instead of 4. I planned it out the night before, charged at my first stop just fine, got here with 6 miles left of range and tried to charge but it wouldn't connect with my car. Tried the other station and the same thing. Called the help number on the printed out piece of paper taped to the charger and he tried resetting the machine. The guy on the other end was nice and helpful, but ultimately we couldn't get it to connect and decided something was incompatible with the the software or hardware between the Spark EV and the charger. Thankfully I brought my level 1 charger and could slowly leech off the outlet at the park shelter nearby. I was able to get enough to get me to the next closest charger.

What was supposed to be a 20 min stop ended up being over 2 hours. We were going to be too late for the party so my family and I just decided to go back home. I have to now check with my credit card because trying to get it to charge put so many $30 holds on it that my credit card stopped working.

The charger in general is okay. The location is good, but I can't see how this is the future for everyone. You have to be quiet strong to manage the thick heavy charging cable. It's much more difficult to plug it in than to use a gas pump or even other fast chargers I've used. I couldn't imagine some of my older relatives having the wrist strength to operate it. And then what? There's no one to help you. It's also not covered, so bring an umbrella if it's raining. I was super excited to use this new charger, because it's been sometimes difficult for someone with a low-range, fast charging EV to get down to Portland and Salem in a reasonable time, but I guess my 7-year old car is too old? This can't be the future of driving.

Great place to stop since there is coffee nearby and McDonald's. Its really sad we see people vandalize the superchargers.

Very slow not sure what the deal is recently but these chargers are way slower than previously.

This is Sheetz. The only. Local place with e85 fuel and tesla  chargers.
See photos? Car on wrecker ? No juice. Dont they really feel stupid now?
It's nice to have an electric charging station near Target. I don't have an electric car but it's nice for anyone who needs their car charged nearby. :)

This charging station belongs to BLINK, which is a total ripoff. They charge $1/hr and it takes at least 4 hours to charge up a Ford C-Max ENERGI, which (fortunately) is a plug-in electric hybrid. Vehicles with a larger capacity battery pack would take considerably longer. At current electric rates in the Pacific NW (6 - 7 cents per KWH) a completely depleted battery pack would cost around 60 cents to charge at home, or 1/7th of what BLINK is demanding. You must apply for and get a plastic magnetic card from them to activate the station. Perhaps the convenience of a fast rate station that charges in 2.5 hours might be worth the rip on occasion, but it's actually cheaper to gas up at the local filling station than to pay BLINK.

Easy to use and friendly staff. Jersey Mike's is a quick walk away and a great stop for lunch.

1-13-2023.   5:30 pm.    Station 1, 3, and 4 are down.   Only #2 is working.

Very fast 250 charging station, almost 40 units. Some aren't in use (covered), and the faster ones have an individual charging box. There's eigjt regular 250 units. The others must be a higher level because we fully charged within an hour and needed over 200 units.

~25 stalls. A lot more capacity than the charger on the other side of the freeway. The hotel is very friendly too. No complaints other than I wish it was a little closer to grab and go food. There‚Äôs a Starbucks and few other places 5-min walk away.
Hard find but easy use and access üòâ
Always open
Convenient and safe parking lot with shops around it
Very busy supercharging spot, 2 chargers are still out of service as of Nov 2022. Would highly recommend Samurai Sushi - delicious and they made our sushi rolls very quickly.

Easy to access using Tesla's navigation system. 250 kw chargers are the best.

All four spaces were available and all chargers were functional.
Very convenient to use, even when towing a trailer. Large parking lot and pull in charger making it easy to charge while towing a trailer.
They almost always work and there's a cumberland farms nearby that's open 24/7

Charged up from 0-75% in aprox. 28 minutes and had an engaging conversation about EV and electric motorbikes with the owner, Rob. Very easy to find in the parking lot behind directly behind the Hilton Garden inn / Courtyard Hotel right off of I-90. CAME BACK  through a week later had to down grade my review from 5 stars. To add insult to injury This seems to be an ongoing problem the #4 charger plug is damaged enough not to work. Probbly from somone not willing to back up enough to plug it in properly in sub zero temperatures  this is Eire Pensyltucky not like it dosn't snow more months a year than it's sunny, for the Californians that designed the supercharger stations. Nice location. In Meijer parking lot. Starbucks inside. It was relaxing and shady today. Getting 350 mi/hr charge.

11/3. Four stations with a 4 x 350 1x50, 3x150 BUT the ONLY station working today is the 150. Also, you can only use ONE pump at a time of the 2 pump station... why is that?? In the Walmart parking lot so it's convenient for shopping .. if you can find a working pump.
I usually don't leave reviews, but wanted to give people some hope with this station. As of writing this I can confirm 4/4 chargers work! Safe travels !

Not getting better from other reviews. Only 1 of the 4 station is worling still. Station 3 btw is the one that works. Lots of frustrated cars here today. It is not just us or our car either a Rivian had the same problem we were waiting for.
Slightly slow but free makes it awesome.

2/4 working when I rolled out.  Possibly vehicle-related issues, but 1 was a blank screen. Pretty typical, hit-or-miss, but look closely at the app for availability, and always keep your expectations...in check, I guess. Lol

This is a convenient charging station at the Walgreens on the corner of Palatine and NW Hwy.  If I had an electric car I would use this station being in a convenient location.  There is a Redbox next to it so you can get a movie.

Nice charging station in affluent South Barrington shopping plaza. Located in the Arhaus parking lot.

Great place to Supercharge. Pride has serval food choices to choose from, restroom and wifi too

Only charging at 70kwh.. great station amenities once service station open, but charging speed is dissapointing as it says 120kwh max speed and we are one of 2 Tesla‚Äôs parked in the 12 stations, so not a capacity problem right now üòê
Charging without issue

EDIT: be warned, if you walk your dogs while charging, the roadside behind the chargers is FULL of all kinds of trash; so be mindful of where they walk.

Decent supercharger mildly off the beaten path, so not as busy as most chargers in the area.

Only saw one person ICE-ing; which surprised me considering this is in the middle of big-boi-truck-country.  A little dimly lit and right at the entrance of the drive-thru, so watch your step if you walk inside at night; a disproportionate amount of drivers fly around the corner into the drive-thru.

Edit: this is clearly out of date, but as a follow-up we told the cashier inside and she immediately went out to mark the charger as being out of order. Good response by the local business!  They get 5 stars.

Good location, but one of the chargers is out of order and with no sign attached there's no quick way to check without plugging in first. A simple sign would save time.  (BTW, it's the one you drive into nose first.)
Love that it says reserved, no ICE cars hogging the spot üëè
There are only 2 available and I had to try both unsuccessfully several times until I luckily got one to let me charge as a guest.
It charged my car. I really wanted something to drink. But it was too cold to go in to Sheetz. There is a 24/7 Dunkin next door!
One of my favorite charging station, so serene!

I came by here at 1:00am needing a boost, but found the charger marked "UNAVAILABLE."  But today I called the Mercedes dealership and the receptionist said it was available to the public 24 hours and was currently marked "AVAILABLE."

Also, according to the ChargePoint agent I spoke with, "UNAVAILABLE" usually means the station is not connected to the Internet preventing it from working with the app, but it should continue to work with the ChargePoint credit card or, possibly, any credit card.

This charger is easy to find. As long as you can access Fort Rucker it‚Äôs a great place to get a fairly quick charge. I averaged about 23 Miles an hour. The other chargers that are supposedly in Enterprise at the car dealerships do not work, so this is about the only option unless you go to Ozark or Dothan.

This level 2. Charging station is in the doctors garage which the public can not access. I had to go to the police desk across the street from Saint Elizabeth Hoapital so the police could escort me down there and open the gate. The charger accepted my Tesla adaptor, and being a level 2 was very slow but very grateful to the Youngstown PD for granting me access..I had enough power to get back to my location.
8 stations.   No waiting for me.  2 were inop but called in

Love these pull-thru locations and this one is at a McDonald's so it a great meal stop when traveling.
CCS 350 worked on the first try. There are window wipers, trash cans, and bathrooms at the Mirabito. Nowhere to sit outside, but the neighborhood is clean and leafy, depending on the season.
Electronics Pkwy charging rate was awesome. Unfortunately, the nearby hotel/convention center is closed, so you have to walk to the Kinney Drugs to use the bathroom.

We have decided the tollway charging is less fun than the Presidential Museum charging stations.  We may be going that way next time.  The Dewitt service plaza has a drainage ditch that runs into a little creek. That was our charging entertainment for this stop.
Love their zchsrging plan and Level 3 charging on the Southside. Very convenient.

The Tesla charger charge at 23 to 25 miles per hour.
Great charger and friendly service! Got to see the new Cadillac Lyriq arrive and ready to roll off the truck!
Always open and fast charging. If you need a full charge be prepared to walk a little if you leave for food or a drink.
Great price and convenient!

Good location, safe area, convenient shopping and restaurants nearby. Found a pair of shoes in the bushes... Not sure what happened but... He ded. üò≥

Great EV charging spot. I've used it several times. I just wish they would add a second charging cable as it's getting harder to use with more EVs on the road and only one spot to charge.

There is a staircase just to the right of the chargers though. Enter the garage near the BBQ restaurant, none of the spots are marked EV and will probably be ICE‚Äôd. If you‚Äôre staying at the Marriott, wait until about 9pm and try again, by that time the restaurant isn‚Äôt as busy and you should be able to get a spot.
Very nice people at location. Though this is not a supercharger.
There are 4 Tesla destination chargers and 2 j1772 chargers.  Very convenient.

Wish I could give them a better rating because the customer service person I spoke with was quite nice. But there are six EVSE units there and at the time I stopped two were down and the other four failed intermittently. Ultimately took an hour or more for me to finally plug in and charge. It doesn't help that CCS public charging is so sparse on the ground in the area, leading to the need to queue during busy periods. Oh well, at least I saw some cool cars (a Lucid and a top spec Taycan) and met some nice people.
Another fast charger 20 mins for over 200 miles. Especially when none else is on the other charger next to you.
Nice location very nice great security cameras
0.20$/minute for charging. Pretty good for my car, got up to very close to max rate and held it for most of the time gaining me about 80 miles in 15 minutes
Charged at 80, nothing to do nearby though..
Super easy to use and thank god cuz I literally had no idea what I was doing. I rented this car and got a 2 min preview of what to do. It‚Äôs been a roller coaster üòÇ

First few times we used this charger was great but this third time was a bit frustrating.

The app shows the quick charger with the CSS and CHADeMO and Tesla connectors ready and the regular chargers as out of service.

But in fact the quick 50W charger only has the CHADeMO connector working but not the CSS or Tesla connectors.  And the level 2 regular chargers were working at the charger itself but not in the app.

Luckily I had the card to tap and charge on the regular chargers but I can't check my charge levels with the app as it shows them out of service. Also the particular level 2 charger I'm using, the locking mechanism doesn't work.

It's too bad that they haven't been maintaining them. As someone visiting from out of state, the app not showing proper updated status of the chargers is very inconvenient.

Other than that, they usually work well and priced moderately, hence 2 stars this time, from 5 stars.
It took my credit card just fine and it was very easy to set up. Only $0.10 per kilowatt hour, awesome compared to electrify America

Honestly not sure what not to dislike about the charging station. Lol
This location is behind a Holiday Inn with 8 charging stations and is very spacious. There isn't much of anything besides the Holiday Inn. It was conveniently located for us and the charging was pretty quick. I had to use the bathroom and the Holiday inn folks nice to let me use their bathroom. There are lights in the parking lot so that was nice not to sit at the door.  Every charging station seems to be in good condition.

So much slower than advertised. You‚Äôre lucky to get 80kW, even with no other cars at adjacent chargers. Not even close to vehicles max allowable charge. Avoid these. The Electrify America in Orangeburg are much faster, almost double.

Most of the time, 3 out 4 of the EVSEs (chargers) are working.  When they are, it is a positive experience.

Love this! Convenient!

Great EV Charging, fast, it's in the jaguar range Rover parking lot, lots of chargers, plus slow chargers as well.
Open to the public, no you do not need an account, you can just tap your credit card and start

Thank you for creating this massive amount of chargers however what is up with the pricing structure?! I used the Level-3 Quick Charge (CCS/SAE Combo) for 5 minutes and only received 2kWh at 40¬¢ per minute!? That would be on the very high side per kWh which is what I thought it must surely be. Nope, per minute. I was charging an e-Golf and only charged at 24-25kW which is extremely low for a Level-3. Please be competitive with Electrify America, EVgo and other ChargePoint stations. I often pay zero, but this is extremely high. I didn't check the cost of the Level-2 as I was very low and didn't want to even entertain waiting here for a few hours. Please revise pricing per kWh and I'll gladly come back as well as update this review. I wound up charging at an Electrify America at the speed of around 50kW (still slow for level-3) at a very high 43¬¢ per kWh with no subscription.
Easy access, convenient to several stores and restaurants. Used this several times, only very busy once (Saturday afternoon).
Super fast, and a nice variety of shops, suggestions to add a trash bin while i wait ( maybe that way my car might be clean lol)

look for a charger for your tesla here you will find it for 60 minutes you can charge it and continue your journey from home to the tesla charger in my direction it is the closest while I put one at home this seems fine to me on Fridays it is always full good at the time I have gone ü•¥.  There are stores where you can go shopping while your Tesla is charging and the security in it Place is good and accessible and a large parking lot so you can take your time away from home
Many open Tesla chargers right next to newly opened travel center.
8 Ports FAST Superchargers with 1 easy forward drive-in port. Long and not easy drive off highway to get to it. Near gas station and many food places that even has gambling machines.

Convenient location as it is not too far off the interstate. They have a trash can and window squeegee available for use at the chargers. Located next to a truck stop that has some food options but not a lot.
Easy to access, plenty of spaces, and a dog area and bucket of window washer fluid is available. Kind of an inconvenient walk to the rest area when snow plowed covered the sidewalks‚Ä¶
Totally works. I can verify 3 types of ports are here
Free charge for electric vehicle. 5 hours to fully charge.
yappers - I did the same while grabbing breakfast at waffle house.  clean and safe area.

Fast charging(250kw) bathrooms and trash receptacles. What more do you need? Well if it is winter and you are headed to OKC you will need to charge somewhere else in addition. Friendly chatty folks here

250kW stalls and easy access to food and restrooms 24/7. Trashcans next to chargers with windshield cleaner water

Have never seen another Tesla changing at the same time. Super empty close to interstate exit, awesome opportunity for stop and charge.

Really kind of this hotel to let anybody who has a Tesla charge here for free. Really nice people, it does motivate you to stay here next time when people are so selfless.  You don‚Äôt need to be a guest to charge at the station, It‚Äôs right in front of reception you can‚Äôt miss it

Best Supercharger location to charge before heading east into the mountains. A clean bathroom is available at the gas station next door. On a busy day, you could drop off family at Ikeda's on the other side of I-80, go charge up, and by the time you're back to Ikeda's you can have lunch or dinner together.
On the way to Reno, we stopped to charge in Auburn. This bowling alley was clean, friendly, and welcoming! Would definitely stop by every chance we can
Good place on the way to Reno

the Level 3 charger was completely off when I got there at 745pm July 11, 2022. there are level 2 chargers that can be used. i used this for an hour to get me enough charge to get to a level 3 charger towards charlotte. disappointing to have the equipment but no level 3 fast charging.
Within walking distance to BJ's restaurant and brewery, Costco, In-n-out, Chipotle and more!
Chargers worked as expected. Plenty of vehicles came and went while we charged. Charging rate was as expected and everyone was considerate of the V2 split charging rule.

This place was empty and fairly quite spot. I went by here late into the night hours and it was very sketchy. I was a bit scared at 1st but then I just played some Taylor Swift and it really calmed me down. Also there are no bathrooms nearby after the Walgreens closes. I think someone might have peed behind one of the dumpsters over there.

Good location, right off Route 287. Has one extra charging stall that can accommodate a storage hitch or bike rack very well. I have been to this charging location numerous time and charging speak were consistent. There is a Dunkin‚Äô Donuts nearby with Wi-Fi access if needed. Many other shops are within walking distance including a McDonald‚Äôs
Had several charging sessions here. Always fast and usually not crowded.

Newly open Tesla Supercharger, not so busy. Approximately 5 minutes drive after exit from Route 46, 80, not so easy to find as it‚Äôs on internal road.

Sign on charting station says 30 minutes ‚ÄúGeneral Parking‚Äù is allowed. There is also a designated Handicap changing station (first time I saw).

On Wawa parking lot, where you can find quick bites, refreshments, restrooms, and cheap gas. Sorry not applicable for Tesla owners!
ChargePoint station works fine. No issues finding it.
Great station for quick top off. Publix and Dollar store are right there to do shopping while car is charging.
Station worked fine for my Bolt EV. $1.38 for 9 kWh. You can walk to breakfast or lunch while picking up a few miles of charge.

The location is at a gas station on the side of the store not too difficult to find. The five stars I‚Äôm giving is because of the easy on and off the interstate, the friendly employees of the store and visited twice and only one other car there. So easy to get in and out quickly with no wait. I forgot to take a pic but there are plenty of good ones here.

Great Tesla Supercharger location that offers fast chargers, a good choice of charge points, and plenty of room if you are towing a trailer. We were lucky and were able to pull straight into a charger slot, but if that wasn‚Äôt possible there was room to drop your trailer.
Charging seemed slow, but my battery was probably too cold. Both the DairyQueen and the Starbucks were good. Excellent charger if you are pulling a trailer.

Probably one of the better supercharger locations I've visited. Clean, high kw, very well let and always a spot to charge. Food nearby was not so good. DO NOT WALK ACROSS THE BIG PARKING LOT TO SI CASA FLORES. Terrible service, terrible food, overpriced.

Wow 51 stalls!!! Biggest SC station I‚Äôve been too. Much needed. With my 75D I could never get to Grants Pass before after Myrtle Creek or Springfield and would have to sleep overnight in Roseburg, now with this we can finally keep moving down and up I5 without hiccup. We got here at 10pm and the Taco Bell and Subway both were still open, subway even has a drive through. Starbucks is also nearby but you have to walk a little further. Decently lit at night.
Good location. There is a grocery store (Myrtle Creek Grocery Outlet, and a few fast food restaurants on site, including McDonald's. No problem finding a bathroom or food.
Easy location to access.

Electrify America (EA) is my go to charge spot! I drive from Pueblo to the Springs and to Denver so I am up and down the front range all week EA has charging stations at every place I need them. Very simple to use and very cheap charging. I love using EA!

I am visiting Pueblo and this is a great location to charge up before heading out to pikes peak, Garden of the Gods, or even Cave of the Wind. As of 20 Oct 2022 this garage is free.

Just trying out the ChragePoint J1772 spot here at San Isabel Electric, there are 2 plugs here. It's on the Northwest end of Pueblo. It's free, but somewhat slow. When I first plugged in I was pulling 3.61Kw, but then after a few minutes charging dropped off to below 1Kw. I stopped the session, and plugged in again, and now I'm pulling a constant 3.61Kw. not sure why it's not pulling more though. Anyways it's free...
Worked great,  charged at 24kw/h and it was free! Spent 20 min,  got 10%!
Close enough to two restaurants to get about 50% charge while you eat.

8x v3 (250kW / "Superfast) Superchargers and Sheetz's tasty MTO food. It's a match made in heaven in an excellent location off of I-95!  Definitely the stop for night time travel too!

The great thing about the fast v3 stalls is that by the time you use the (usually) clean toilets, place an order for hot food and then receive it, your Tesla is done with its snack and is good for the next leg of your trip. This Sheetz, like most others, has fantastic staff, a clean layout, and toilets you can access 24/7 (unlike strip mall based charging stops). It's also large enough to have an eating area so if you want to chill for a little longer and enjoy your greasy messy Big Mozz sandwich or something you can do so without getting your car all dirty. :)

Traffic can be a little heavy at times, since this is a very good location for any kind of fueling up, but bonus points for putting the charging stalls near the drive-thru lane. Most of the non-tesla traffic on this side of the building is in the separate drive way to place the order which makes pulling into a spot a little easier. This partnership with Sheetz just gets better and smarter all the time!

Not quite the best spot to charge before bailing onto 295 and avoiding the Richmond mess, but it's not far. You can do a short hop back to get to 295 or take the major local roads to meet back up with it!
Always is clean and the Sheetz gas station is open 24/7 they do have seating/eating area inside. Nice area to stop and take a break from the road and of course to charge up your Tesla
A bit on the slow side but at least Wawa is right near by for a quick stop
Target charger is great. Costco one has never worked.
Charging worked easily with the Charge point app and was free. Nice shady sitting area nearby. The only downside is that there aren't any coffee shops or restaurants within walking distance.
350kwh charger #2 errored out and did not work. 350kwh charger #3 only charged at 108kwh rate. Rivian r1t battery prepped for charging, began at 24% battery. Should have been over 200kwh charge rate.
I get a real charge at these places.
Thank you H-E-B!! Ten, yes 10, charging stations. Great location just off I-10! Easy access and easy to find!

Super great location! It's only been open a month and we used it coming from Austin to fburg. It's near a subway and dollar general, in the same parking lot. The dollar general says no public bathrooms so we ran across the highway üò¨ to use valero's while we waited. 1,unisex stall.

It‚Äôs OPEN. The main entrance to the casino is closed but you can drive down the driveway you normally exit from to get to the super charger. There is usually a security vehicle there to police that only Tesla‚Äôs are entering the grounds
It was more expensive than other chargers I've used, but it worked reliably.
These stations are a little off the beaten path. No signs to direct you. They charge $2.50 per hour @ level 2 which seems to be pretty expensive. Parking meter rates in the area are $1 per hour.

It has a canopy so you are sheltered from the rain. It is also in the parking lot of a decent sized gas station. It is well lit and clean.  We got there around 10:30 pm on a Friday night. The gas station was busy as if it was the middle of the day. This station had ample snacks and drinks, like the perfect place to charge and get refreshments for yourself. The charging area wasn't crowded, so we got in easily. I would definitely recommend this if you are in the area!

Probably the best super charger in SC. Easy to get in and out.

Right next to the Spinx gas station with tidy restrooms.

All V3 super chargers as well.

Charging was SUPER slow at this location. The restroom in Clarks restaurant was clean. The gift shop was cute and gave me something to look at while charging. A trash can was available and had room for more trash.
Easy highway access location with walkable ameneities. Charged around 100 kW. Staff at Lodging adjacent to chargers were kind and allowed use of clean bathrooms.

8 chargers just off I-95 at a Texaco station with a Stuckey's convenience store that houses a Dairy Queen. Bathroom was a bit gross but, hey, at least it was working! Depending on how you feel about guns and machismo, you will either feel right at home here or anxious to leave.

Looked clean and was nice quick stop for a charge and some snacks during the day. Drove by at night and needs more lighting to feel more secure. We‚Äôre plenty of open spaces and the dog park was open.
Chargers worked great...people inside at Casey's were nice...great seletion for a small store. Nice to see the gas/electric stations starting to pop up.
Clean, love the super chargers
Good location off of i20 and in a Publix parking lot. This location is busy during rush hour.
Great location by Publix, it actually needs to be bigger. They have space to expand.
Good clean amenities. Charging started out fast. One of the chargers gave an error. Recommend heading across the street for Wheat Jesus.

Destination charger not working. Went there about an hour before opening. Not sure why Tesla would direct us there if they are for customers only (which we were willing to be) just a heads up for others that may need a charge in the area.
Nice location. Steak and shake next door and a 24/7 place across the street. Parking lots to walk around in and functional chargers.
It was a supercharger. It was about 50% utilized and got to meet some other nice Tesla owner.

Squeegee and trash provided by Hyvee. Trash was filled to the brim! We took advantage of the huge tent and table with chairs near the Suc and had our lunch there out of the car. Assume they use this for pickup of garden items when in season. A little far off I-90 but still a nice stop!
50 amp ccs, brand new polestar 2.  53-90%  20 min.  Seamless, started charging immediately after pushing start.

This supercharger is located in the downtown of Ukiah. In the daytime I felt safe it was a little confusing to get to and I felt a little nervous that I didn‚Äôt know where I was going or if this town even had a supercharger but it does there‚Äôs not many superchargers but it‚Äôs not a credit one there are eight superchargers. There is a trashcan right here in the parking lot which was very nice a lot of superchargers did not have trash cans but again like I said there was no public restroom that I can see within a few steps away.
Outstanding + new fast chargers
I appreciate that they added a portapotty for when the Sage center is closed. No food but otherwise a nice spot to stop. Someone put real effort into plowing their giant parking lot.

Right off the freeway and easy to find. Near casino which always seems to be busy, but I was left well enough alone. Mcdonald's is a short walk away as well as the casino. It was quite windy both times I passed through as I imagine is quite common.
Easy and inexpensive with the volta app. Wegmans has a bathroom and snacks to buy. Good stop.

The only thing I'd like to see added is a roof or something that gives some shade on a hot summer day.
I parked next to the station today while waiting for my wife in TJ Maxx and munching on a fresh bagel and cream cheese and realized... Filling up is no longer an in and out thing! No others when arrived, but all 4 stations in use at once within the hour my Bolt needed and only one remained when Ieft.

This charging station is the last place I fill up going over the mountain from Portland to Bend. There is one Chademo connector and one J1772 connector here. The rest of the plugs are CCS. I've only charged with the CCS at this location. There is no reason to charge with the J1772 plug here unless the Volta station nearby is full or you plan on charging longer than 2 hours. The CCS cables here aren't very long, so if your charging port is in the rear of your vehicle I would suggest backing into the charging stall. The cables here are also exceptionally bulky and heavy because they are liquid cooled. The liquid cooling is needed to keep the cables from getting too hot at the high charging rates this station is capable of producing. The pricing here is standard Electrify America rates for Oregon. A word of warning to users having issues with getting a charge to start here: The cables are very heavy and don't always make a perfect connection with some cars like the Chevy Bolt. This causes a connection error at the start of the charge. The solution is to hold up gently on the CCS cable and activate charging in the app while continuing the gentle upward pressure on the cable until the charging starts. This is indicated by a green blinking light on the Bolt dash.

Front row parking is really nice. Free to use. In case some people are wondering, yes you can charge all day while at the park. You don‚Äôt have to move the vehicle when charging is complete. There are plenty of spots to charge.
Also, these chargers are on a shared load. What that means is if you‚Äôre the only Tesla charging, you‚Äôll get the full 46amps. If other Tesla‚Äôs are charging, the load is not only shared, but managed by the software as well. So if you have a very low state of charge and the car next to you is mostly charged, the lower charged car will receive a lot more juice to charge faster, while the other car is still charging but at a lower rate. It‚Äôs normal to see charging amps change frequently in your app.

This has worked for me a few times and is in a good location, but out of the many charging stations I‚Äôve used, I like the Webasto / AV network by far the least (which is what is at this location). The app PlugShare has been a lifesaver for finding alternatives and is very user friendly. The chargepoint charger by tofurkey hq is a much better option.

The phone call required to start up Webasto stations as a non-member tends to take a full 10 minutes every time - other brands‚Äô stations (blink, chargepoint, Volta) do not require a call to start, so having to call and wait on hold seems like a pretty unnecessary hassle.

Webasto are also the only brand of chargers that has been unreliable for me - today, this charger did not work, and I had one instance elsewhere where the charger inexplicably timed out. In both cases, calling customer service to troubleshoot was pretty frustrating - today, the rep insisted the problem was my car and not the station, even though 2 other brands of stations had worked for me in the past day. Immediately after our call I drove to a chargepoint station which worked successfully, so I followed up and informed Webasto that the problem was indeed their charger, not my car.

I am hoping Webasto addresses this issue - this location is so convenient and I‚Äôd love to charge here. Based on my experience and frustrations with the company though, I‚Äôll be charging elsewhere when available - have never had any reliability or customer service issues with other companies.
